    <div class="container">
      <h2>Our Stamped Concrete Projects</h2>
      <div class="image-grid">
        {projectImages.map((image, index) => (
          <div class="image-item">
            <img src={image} alt={`Stamped concrete project ${index + 1} in Deptford, NJ`} loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What is Stamped Concrete?</h2>
      <p>Stamped concrete is a decorative concrete technique that creates beautiful patterns and textures, mimicking the look of natural stone, brick, tile, or wood. This cost-effective solution transforms ordinary concrete into stunning surfaces that enhance the beauty and value of your property.</p>

      <h3>Stamped Concrete Applications</h3>
      <p>We install stamped concrete for a variety of outdoor applications throughout Deptford and surrounding New Jersey communities:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stamped Concrete Patios:</strong> Create beautiful outdoor living spaces with decorative patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Stamped Concrete Driveways:</strong> Enhance curb appeal with elegant driveway designs</li>
        <li><strong>Stamped Concrete Walkways:</strong> Add visual interest to pathways and sidewalks</li>
        <li><strong>Pool Decks:</strong> Slip-resistant stamped concrete for pool areas</li>
        <li><strong>Outdoor Kitchens:</strong> Durable stamped concrete for outdoor cooking areas</li>
        <li><strong>Commercial Spaces:</strong> Decorative concrete for businesses and commercial properties</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Popular Stamped Concrete Patterns</h3>
      <p>Choose from a wide variety of patterns and textures to match your style:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ashlar Slate - Classic stone appearance</li>
        <li>Herringbone - Elegant brick pattern</li>
        <li>Wood Plank - Warm wood grain texture</li>
        <li>Cobblestone - Old-world charm</li>
        <li>Flagstone - Natural stone look</li>
        <li>Random Stone - Varied natural appearance</li>
        <li>And many more custom patterns</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Benefits of Stamped Concrete</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cost-Effective:</strong> More affordable than natural stone or pavers</li>
        <li><strong>Durable:</strong> Long-lasting and low-maintenance</li>
        <li><strong>Versatile:</strong> Wide variety of patterns and colors</li>
        <li><strong>Customizable:</strong> Can match your home's style and color scheme</li>
        <li><strong>Slip-Resistant:</strong> Safe for pool decks and walkways</li>
        <li><strong>Value-Adding:</strong> Increases property value and curb appeal</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What's Included in Our Stamped Concrete Service</h3>
      <p>When you choose Deptford Concrete Contractors for your stamped concrete project, you receive comprehensive service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Free Design Consultation:</strong> We help you choose the perfect pattern, color, and design to match your style</li>
        <li><strong>Custom Design:</strong> Stamped concrete design tailored to your property and aesthetic preferences</li>
        <li><strong>Site Preparation:</strong> Proper excavation, grading, and base preparation to ensure your stamped concrete lasts</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Materials:</strong> High-grade concrete mixes and color additives designed for decorative applications</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Expert installation by experienced concrete professionals skilled in stamping techniques</li>
        <li><strong>Pattern Application:</strong> Precise stamping to create your chosen pattern and texture</li>
        <li><strong>Coloring Services:</strong> Integral color mixing or surface treatments to achieve your desired appearance</li>
        <li><strong>Sealing:</strong> Professional sealant application to protect your stamped concrete and enhance its appearance</li>
        <li><strong>Expansion Joints:</strong> Properly placed expansion joints to prevent cracking from temperature changes</li>
        <li><strong>Cleanup:</strong> Complete site cleanup after installation</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance Guidance:</strong> Advice on proper care, cleaning, and resealing to maintain your stamped concrete's beauty</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Our Stamped Concrete Installation Process</h3>
      <p>We follow a detailed process to ensure your stamped concrete is installed correctly and beautifully:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Design Consultation:</strong> We discuss your vision, show pattern options, and help you choose the perfect design</li>
        <li><strong>Site Evaluation:</strong> We assess your property, drainage patterns, and local requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Permit Assistance:</strong> We help secure necessary permits if required by your municipality</li>
        <li><strong>Site Preparation:</strong> Professional excavation and proper base material installation for stability</li>
        <li><strong>Formwork:</strong> Installation of forms to create your stamped concrete's shape and boundaries</li>
        <li><strong>Concrete Pouring:</strong> Placement of high-quality concrete mix with color additives if using integral color</li>
        <li><strong>Stamping:</strong> Precise application of stamping tools to create your chosen pattern and texture</li>
        <li><strong>Coloring (if surface treatment):</strong> Application of color hardeners or release agents for desired appearance</li>
        <li><strong>Finishing:</strong> Proper finishing and texturing to complete the stamped appearance</li>
        <li><strong>Curing:</strong> Proper curing time to ensure maximum strength and durability</li>
        <li><strong>Sealing:</strong> Professional sealant application to protect and enhance your stamped concrete</li>
        <li><strong>Final Inspection:</strong> Quality check to ensure your stamped concrete meets all standards</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Common Issues Stamped Concrete Solves</h3>
      <p>Stamped concrete addresses many common outdoor surface needs:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>High Cost of Natural Stone:</strong> Stamped concrete provides the look of natural stone at a fraction of the cost</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance Challenges:</strong> Stamped concrete is easier to maintain than pavers or natural stone</li>
        <li><strong>Limited Design Options:</strong> Wide variety of patterns and colors allows for custom designs</li>
        <li><strong>Low Curb Appeal:</strong> Beautiful stamped concrete significantly enhances property appearance and value</li>
        <li><strong>Durability Concerns:</strong> Stamped concrete is highly durable and withstands New Jersey's climate</li>
        <li><strong>Installation Complexity:</strong> Professional installation ensures proper pattern application and sealing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What Happens When You Call</h3>
      <p>Getting your stamped concrete installed is straightforward with our streamlined process:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Initial Contact (24-48 Hour Response):</strong> When you reach out via phone or our contact form, we'll respond within 24-48 hours to schedule your free estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Free On-Site Estimate:</strong> We visit your property to assess your space, discuss pattern options, and provide a detailed written estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Project Planning:</strong> Once you approve the estimate, we handle all planning including permits (if needed), material ordering, and scheduling</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Our experienced team completes your stamped concrete installation efficiently and professionally</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Our Customer Service Promise</h3>
      <p>At Deptford Concrete Contractors, we believe in complete transparency and honest communication:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Hidden Fees:</strong> Your written estimate includes all costs - materials, labor, stamping, coloring, sealing, and cleanup - no surprises</li>
        <li><strong>Clear Communication:</strong> We keep you informed at every step, from initial estimate through project completion</li>
        <li><strong>Realistic Timelines:</strong> We provide honest timelines based on project scope and weather conditions - typically 1-2 days for most stamped concrete projects</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Guarantee:</strong> We stand behind our work and ensure your stamped concrete meets all quality and code standards</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive Service:</strong> We respond to questions and concerns promptly, typically within 24-48 hours</li>
        <li><strong>Licensed & Insured:</strong> Full professional coverage protects you and your property throughout the project</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Stamped Concrete Investment Factors</h3>
      <p>Understanding what affects your stamped concrete investment helps you make informed decisions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Size and Complexity:</strong> Larger areas or complex designs require more materials and labor</li>
        <li><strong>Pattern Choice:</strong> Some patterns are more complex and may require additional time</li>
        <li><strong>Color Options:</strong> Integral color mixing or multiple colors can affect cost</li>
        <li><strong>Site Preparation:</strong> Challenging terrain or extensive excavation affects cost</li>
        <li><strong>Sealing Requirements:</strong> Professional sealing is essential and included in all estimates</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Difficult access may require special equipment or additional time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We provide free, detailed estimates that break down all costs so you understand exactly what you're investing in. There are no hidden fees or surprise charges - what we quote is what you pay.</p>

      <h3>Maintenance Tips</h3>
      <p>Stamped concrete is low-maintenance but benefits from occasional care:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Regular cleaning with mild detergent and water</li>
        <li>Resealing every 2-3 years to maintain appearance and protection</li>
        <li>Avoiding harsh chemicals or de-icers that can damage the sealant</li>
        <li>Protecting from heavy impact or dragging heavy objects</li>
        <li>Prompt repair of any minor cracks to prevent water damage</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Related Services</h3>
      <p>Stamped concrete is perfect for various outdoor applications:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/services/patios">Patio Installation</a> - Stamped concrete patios</li>
        <li><a href="/services/driveways">Driveway Installation</a> - Stamped concrete driveways</li>
        <li><a href="/services/walkways">Walkway Installation</a> - Decorative pathways</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Areas We Serve</h3>
      <p>We provide stamped concrete installation services throughout <a href="/locations/deptford-nj">Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/west-deptford-nj">West Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/woodbury-nj">Woodbury</a>, <a href="/locations/glassboro-nj">Glassboro</a>, and <a href="/locations">all surrounding Gloucester County communities</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

