  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Stamped Concrete FAQs</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does stamped concrete last?</h3>
          <p>Properly installed and maintained stamped concrete can last 25-30 years or more. Regular resealing every 2-3 years helps maintain its appearance and durability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How much does stamped concrete cost compared to natural stone?</h3>
          <p>Stamped concrete typically costs significantly less than natural stone or pavers while providing a similar appearance. The exact savings depend on the pattern and area size.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can stamped concrete be repaired if it cracks?</h3>
          <p>Yes, minor cracks in stamped concrete can often be repaired to match the existing pattern. We'll assess any damage during maintenance and recommend the best repair approach.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How often does stamped concrete need to be resealed?</h3>
          <p>Stamped concrete should be resealed every 2-3 years to maintain its appearance and protect against wear, weather, and staining. We provide maintenance guidance after installation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is stamped concrete slippery when wet?</h3>
          <p>Properly sealed stamped concrete can be slippery when wet, but we can apply non-slip additives or use textured patterns for areas like pool decks where safety is a concern.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

